phase1.code:
package main

import "fmt"

func main() {
    health := 75

    // ---- Basic if ----
    if health > 50 {
        fmt.Println("You are healthy!")
    }

    // ---- if/else ----
    if health > 50 {
        fmt.Println("You are healthy!")
    } else {
        fmt.Println("You are wounded.")
    }

    // ---- if/else-if/else ----
    if health > 80 {
        fmt.Println("You are at full health!")
    } else if health > 50 {
        fmt.Println("You are wounded, but okay.")
    } else if health > 20 {
        fmt.Println("You are badly hurt.")
    } else {
        fmt.Println("You are near death!")
    }

    // ---- if with statement ----
    if score := 85; score >= 80 {
        fmt.Println("Score is excellent!")
    }

    // ---- if with multiple conditions ----
    hasKey := true
    hasSword := false

    if hasKey && hasSword {
        fmt.Println("You can enter the boss room!")
    } else if hasKey {
        fmt.Println("You have the key, but no sword.")
    } else if hasSword {
        fmt.Println("You have a sword, but no key.")
    } else {
        fmt.Println("You have nothing.")
    }

    // ---- if with OR ----
    if health < 20 || hasKey {
        fmt.Println("Something is happening...")
    }

    // ---- if without braces? No, braces are required ----
    // In Go, braces are always required

    // ---- Short variable declaration in if ----
    if err := process(); err != nil {
        fmt.Println("Error:", err)
    } else {
        fmt.Println("Success!")
    }
}

func process() error {
    return nil
}

phase1.explanation:
🦫 **if/else controls the flow of your program.**

**if syntax:**
```go
if condition {
    // runs if true
}
```

**if/else:**
```go
if condition {
    // runs if true
} else {
    // runs if false
}
```

**if with statement:**
```go
if x := 5; x > 0 {
    // x is scoped to the if block
}
```

**Go-chan says:**
"Braces are required. No exceptions."

**Rules:**
- Conditions don't need parentheses
- Braces are always required
- Variables declared in the if statement are scoped to the if/else blocks
- `else` must be on the same line as the closing brace

